title._content: Highway traffic on a road near Newport Beach, May 1975

description._content: Original Caption: Highway traffic on a road near Newport Beach. Road widening in this area has occurred in the past few years as a large shopping center and business complex was developed above the all residential area at the harbor. Regulation of development within 1,000 yards of the coastline has resulted in increasing restrictions since the implementation of the Coastal Zone Conservation Act in early 1973 in California, May 1975 U.S. National Archives’ Local Identifier: 412-DA-14979 Photographer: O'Rear, Charles, 1941- Subjects: Los Angeles (California) Environmental Protection Agency Project DOCUMERICA Persistent URL: research.archives.gov/description/557431 Repository: Still Picture Records Section, Special Media Archives Services Division (NWCS-S), National Archives at College Park, 8601 Adelphi Road, College Park, MD, 20740-6001.
